snippet.textDisplay: Boxing fan rant:boxing fans read and tell me your thoughts.. I watch matches often with the sound off because commentators are bias and I'ma fan of the sport itself the beautiful science of boxing only.. Not a wilder or fury fan..but i feel no one saw the fight i saw or didn't care that fury was using illegal life threatening punches thru the fight.. I challenge any fan to re watch the fight with sound off. Wilder won first 2 rounds then towards ending of 2nd fury started to repeatedly connect with medium power to full power punches connecting to back of wilders head and back of ear/base of skull which immediately started to affect his standing and balance more than beginning jitters. I counted 5 times this happen before he was knocked down  with the 6th same illegal punch  to the back of the head..not a clean head or face shot direct punch connecting to back of head/base of skull only,  knocking wilder down..Wilder immediately looked at the ref like your not gonna call that and yells toward him. The ref purposely turned his back to wilder after the punch neglecting the call which is odd because fury wasn't next to wilder and typically the ref goes to the fallen boxer to start a count immediately after clearing the fighter. He didn't and faced fury the whole time as if he was talking to him.This was crazy to watch as a boxing fan because the ref did not 1 time call this foul , take a point or stop fury from doing it. After the first knock down i counted 9 more times fury purposely hit wilder in back of head and base of skull.  After his ear started bleeding fury even targeted the ear directly punching wilder in the ear when it started bleeding that would be considered dirty to most fighters i thought. Which hitting the ear in and  of if self is not illegal or dirty and by all means if you see blood eat. But the cause of the bleeding is what i want ppl to think about for it to be bleeding 1 of 2 things has most likely  happen in that situation..1. his ear drum has burst or 2. the back of his skull is fractured causing bleeding thru ear judging on the amount blood coming out of ear and swelling of head itself around ear... Which any these and other issues where from the result of illegal punches to back of ear/base of skull and back of head.. Now if you throw a illegal punch of any sort to my understanding in boxing lets say for example a punch below the belt after the 3rd or 4th time of being warned or points being taken away you are disqualified. Fury did this no less than 15 times unchecked. And not taps to back of head i mean jabs, crosses some of which  where initially misses but fury would continue the punch to connect.(example a boxer throws a jab the other fighter moves head down the average fighter misses target of head or face pulls jab or cross back moves feet either pivots, steps back ,lean back or pursue after pulling back jab or cross, Fury on other hand throws jab or cross misses face/head. fury then further extends and steps in to same punch not taking it back and stepping further to his outside/side and ending up behind him in a lot of cases and only connecting to the exposed back of wilders head /base of skull and general area behind ear. On other occasions punching wilder from back of shoulder alot of times elbowing his neck and base of skull after by following thru semi illegally because you cannot elbow or for arm a fighter to neck or back of head directly. No matter the stage of extension of fury punch at the moment this is connecting to the back of wilders head  in motion in 2 directions while  dodging fury punch. 1)while he is ducking his head down or 2)while he is popping it back up but wilder is being hit in the back of the head when this happens. Just think about leaning your head under a desk raising it up real quick only to hit the back of your head on the table or bowing your head and someone throws a dictionary on the back of your head get it.. direct force to back of head stuns brain directly more soft tissue further reasons these punches are not allowed.
